          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-9119 lnet: add timeout to dynamic discovery thread",
        "message": "LU-9119 lnet: add timeout to dynamic discovery thread\n\nIn order to avoid the scenario where a peer remains on the\nworking queue forever due to not receiving an ACK or a REPLY\nwake up every 1 second and check the work queue for peers\nthat have been waiting for >= the DEFAULT_PEER_TIMEOUT.\nStop once we find a peer that has not expired since the peers\nare added in chronological order to the queue.\nExpired peers are moved to the new expired queue, and the MDs\nfor their outstanding Ping and Push operations unlinked. The\nevent handler for LNET_EVENT_UNLINK checks if the operation\ndid indeed fail to complete, and if so, generates the timeout\nerror. Peer state will be UNDISCOVERED after a timeout.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <amir.shehata@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Olaf Weber <olaf@sgi.com>\nChange-Id: If2da380b17d14d0066e3cd678cd2b849d5ec820d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
  },
